{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882330271,"sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad5e09c001JkiPeLdvgVxfMK","messageID":"msg_d7ad5d885001tu3RSs5f1euols","sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775882330917,"sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad5e21f001Lpbs5CDJPKfGqx","messageID":"msg_d7ad5d885001tu3RSs5f1euols","sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough understanding. Let me write the proposal.md.","time":{"start":1775882330915,"end":1775882330915}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882349728,"sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad5e3250015C4nJYx8RXhHEU","messageID":"msg_d7ad5d885001tu3RSs5f1euols","sessionID":"ses_2852af65bffej6j1KWUCMrG2mO","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3df4de0bd25a44a5a423ac42","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-039: Go Unit Tests (router/store/picod)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal outlines the implementation of comprehensive unit tests for three core components in the agentcube project:\n\n1. **router** - HTTP routing and proxy layer (`pkg/router/`)\n2. **store** - Data persistence layer using Valkey/Redis (`pkg/store/`)\n3. **picod** - PicoD execution server (`pkg/picod/`)\n\nThe goal is to achieve **>80% code coverage** for these modules, ensure critical business logic is properly tested, and prevent regressions during future development.\n\n## Scope\n\n### Router (`pkg/router/`)\n\n**Existing tests:** 167 lines covering basic initialization and simple scenarios.\n\n**Tests to add:**\n- `backend.go` - Backend pool management, health checking, header-based routing\n- `proxy.go` - Proxy forwarding, connection handling, timeout behavior\n- `route.go` - Route matching logic, path prefix handling\n- `ratelimit.go` - Rate limiting algorithm, token bucket implementation\n- `auth.go` - Token authentication flow\n- `jwt.go`, `jwt_handler.go`, `jwt_middleware.go` - JWT validation, token refresh\n- `session.go`, `session_middleware.go` - Session lifecycle, cookie handling\n- `logging.go` - Request/response logging\n- `health.go` - Health check endpoint\n\n**Coverage targets:**\n- `server.go` - Expand from basic tests to full lifecycle testing\n- All middleware components\n\n### Store (`pkg/store/`)\n\n**Existing tests:** None.\n\n**Tests to add:**\n- `store.go` - Interface definitions and contract tests\n- `store_valkey.go` - All Store interface implementations using mock Valkey client\n- `store_redis.go` - Redis-specific implementations (if applicable)\n- `errors.go` - Error type assertions\n\n**Testing strategy:**\n- Use `valkey-go` embedded mock or interface-based testing\n- Test each Store method: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, `Close`\n- Test edge cases: empty session ID, expired sandbox, concurrent updates\n\n**Coverage targets:**\n- Minimum 90% coverage for store implementations\n\n### PicoD (`pkg/picod/`)\n\n**Existing tests:** 833 lines covering execution, file operations, auth.\n\n**Tests to add:**\n- `execute.go` - Command execution, timeout handling, environment variables\n- `files.go` - Additional file operation edge cases\n- `auth.go` - Auth manager edge cases\n- `config.go` - Config validation edge cases\n\n**Coverage targets:**\n- Expand existing handler tests to cover more error paths\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Benefits\n\n1. **Improved Code Quality** - Tests catch bugs before production deployment\n2. **Regression Prevention** - CI pipeline will fail on breaking changes\n3. **Documentation** - Tests serve as executable documentation of expected behavior\n4. **Refactoring Safety** - Enables safe code refactoring with confidence\n5. **Debugging** - Faster root cause analysis when issues occur\n\n### Risks\n\n1. **Test Maintenance** - Tests require updates when implementation changes\n2. **Flaky Tests** - Need careful handling of timeouts and async operations\n3. **Mock Complexity** - Store tests may require extensive mocking of Valkey/Redis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- Standard Go testing (`testing` package)\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` for assertions\n- Existing test infrastructure (see `pkg/router/server_test.go`, `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Integration Tests Only\n- **Rejected:** Too slow for TDD, require external services (Valkey/Redis)\n\n### 2. Property-Based Testing\n- **Deferred:** Could be added later using `testing/quick` or `github.com/leanovate/gopter`\n\n### 3. Third-Party Testing Frameworks (ginkgo, testify)\n- **Decision:** Use standard `testing` package with `testify/assert` for assertions (matches existing project style)\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Phase 1: Router Tests**\n   - Add `*_test.go` files for each component\n   - Focus on business logic (backend pool, rate limiting, routing)\n\n2. **Phase 2: Store Tests**\n   - Create interface mocks\n   - Implement tests for all Store methods\n\n3. **Phase 3: PicoD Gap Coverage**\n   - Fill remaining coverage gaps in existing test files\n\n4. **Phase 4: CI Integration**\n   - Ensure tests run in `make test` target\n   - Add coverage reporting\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/*_test.go     # New + existing\npkg/store/store_test.go       # NEW\npkg/store/store_valkey_test.go  # NEW\npkg/picod/*_test.go     # Expand existing\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Router: >80% line coverage\n- [ ] Store: >90% line coverage  \n- [ ] PicoD: >85% line coverage (expand existing)\n- [ ] All tests pass: `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n- [ ] No flaky tests (deterministic results)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775882349718,"end":1775882349725}}}}
